cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MM 

This paper is about optimizing the training of a cascade classifier for object detection, which is a common task in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new boosting algorithm that optimizes a cost function, which is a machine learning (ML) technique. Hence, cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also uses convex optimization techniques, which fall under the sub-category cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on object detection, which is a common application of multimedia (MM) technologies, making cs.MM a possible sub-category as well.
